/**
\page kernel_catalog Kernel Catalog

The kernel catalog is described by \c kernels/manifest.json — the
authoritative machine-readable index covering kernel names, argument
metadata, backend availability, launch defaults, and capability
requirements.

\section kernel_catalog_domains Domains

- Algebraic multigrid: 16 kernels
- BLAS / dense linear algebra: 2 kernels
- Distributed communication: 20 kernels
- Linear solvers: 409 kernels
- Miscellaneous: 1409 kernels
- Neural / spectral operators: 12 kernels
- Parallel primitives: 14 kernels
- Sparse linear algebra: 54 kernels
- Volume-of-Fluid CFD: 157 kernels

\section kernel_catalog_usage Usage

Application code should prefer the stable wrapper APIs or the host
registry over direct per-file source parsing. The raw kernel files are
still useful for inspection, debugging, or porting to a new backend.

\section kernel_catalog_limitations Limitations

Backend coverage is not uniform. See \c docs/BACKEND_COVERAGE.md for
the current matrix and \c docs/KERNEL_INDEX.md for the domain index.
Numerical validation is tracked separately from source coverage.
*/
